abstract: TransCanada Inc, developer of Keystone XL pipeline, is changing its plans in Nebraska, abandoning efforts to invoke eminent domain through courts; will instead seek approval for pipeline's routes through Nebraska Public Service Commission.
lead_paragraph: TransCanada Inc. said it would abandon its efforts to invoke eminent domain through the courts in Nebraska and will reapply for approval through the state’s Public Service Commission.
